            <section class="py-3">
                <div class="container">
                    <article class="bg-content p-3 rounded">
                        <h1 class="fs-4 fw-bold mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>

                        <p><strong>Last updated: June 24, 2025</strong></p>

                        <h2 class="fs-5 fw-bold">GENERAL INFORMATION</h2>
                        <p>At Merge Rot, we prioritize the privacy of all users who access our website and applications. This Privacy Policy applies to all services and products offered through the Merge Rot platform. Please note that we are not responsible for the privacy practices of other sites. Merge Rot will act as the data controller within the framework of this policy. By using our site, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy and confirm that you are of legal age to provide consent. Continued use of the site after significant changes to this policy indicates your acceptance of the updated terms. We are committed to treating your personal information with confidentiality.</p>

                        <p>The Merge Rot website is intended for visitors aged 16 and above. If you are under 16, please do not use our site. By accessing Merge Rot, you agree to comply with this Privacy Policy and consent to the collection and use of your data as outlined herein. Parents or legal guardians permitting their children to access Merge Rot are also consenting to this policy on their behalf.</p>

                        <p>We value your trust and take our responsibility seriously. This document explains what information we collect, why we collect it, and how it is used to enhance your experience. For any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at <strong>support@mergerot.co</strong>.</p>

                        <h2 class="fs-5 fw-bold">WHICH DATA DO WE COLLECT?</h2>

                        <h3 class="fs-6 fw-bold">Data You Provide</h3>
                        <p>We process personal data that you voluntarily provide when filling out forms on our site or contacting us via email. This may include:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Name</strong>: Identifies you in our communications.</li>
                            <li><strong>Email Address</strong>: Used for correspondence and updates.</li>
                            <li><strong>Other Information</strong>: Any additional details you choose to share.</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="fs-6 fw-bold">Data We Collect Automatically</h3>
                        <p>We may collect certain personal data automatically through cookies and other tracking technologies. This data, accessible only during your visit, may include:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>IP Address</strong>: Helps prevent double voting and supports location-based advertising.</li>
                            <li><strong>Browser Type and Version</strong>: Information about your web browser.</li>
                            <li><strong>Last Visited Web Page</strong>: The previous page you visited before Merge Rot.</li>
                            <li><strong>Device IDs</strong>: Identifiers for your mobile or desktop device.</li>
                            <li><strong>Cookie Data</strong>: Information stored in cookies.</li>
                            <li><strong>User Activity Data</strong>: Such as interactions with advertisements.</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="fs-6 fw-bold">Data We Receive from Third Parties</h3>
                        <p>If we receive personal information from third parties, we will notify you directly.</p>

                        <h2 class="fs-5 fw-bold">WHY DO WE COLLECT THIS DATA?</h2>
                        <p>We collect your personal data to optimize our services and content. The legal grounds for processing this data include:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Contractual Necessity</strong>: To fulfill our obligations to you.</li>
                            <li><strong>Your Consent</strong>: Where applicable, you provide explicit permission.</li>
                            <li><strong>Legitimate Interests</strong>: We process data to pursue legitimate business interests, provided these do not override your rights.</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2 class="fs-5 fw-bold">DATA RETENTION PERIODS</h2>
                        <p>Your personal data will be processed only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy. Data will be deleted one month after a period of consecutive years without access to our site, unless we have a legitimate reason to retain it.</p>

                        <h2 class="fs-5 fw-bold">LEGAL BASIS FOR PROCESSING PERSONAL DATA UNDER GDPR</h2>
                        <p>For users from the European Economic Area (EEA), our legal basis for collecting and using personal information depends on the context of the data collection. We may process your data because:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>We need to perform a contract.</li>
                            <li>You have given us your permission.</li>
                            <li>Processing is in our legitimate interests.</li>
                            <li>We must comply with the law.</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2 class="fs-5 fw-bold">YOUR DATA PROTECTION RIGHTS UNDER GDPR</h2>
                        <p>If you are an EEA resident, you have specific data protection rights, including:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Access</strong>: Request access to your personal data.</li>
                            <li><strong>Rectification</strong>: Request correction of inaccurate information.</li>
                            <li><strong>Objection</strong>: Object to our processing of your data.</li>
                            <li><strong>Restriction</strong>: Request restriction on data processing.</li>
                            <li><strong>Data Portability</strong>: Request a copy of your data in a machine-readable format.</li>
                            <li><strong>Withdraw Consent</strong>: Withdraw consent at any time.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>For any requests regarding your data, please contact us.</p>

                        <h2 class="fs-5 fw-bold">YOUR RIGHTS</h2>
                        <p>You can opt out of newsletters or information about our products at any time. To request rectification or deletion of your data, please provide a reason for your request. We will process your request promptly once verified.</p>

                        <h2 class="fs-5 fw-bold">COOKIES</h2>

                        <h3 class="fs-6 fw-bold">What Are Cookies?</h3>
                        <p>Cookies are small files stored on your device when you visit websites. They contain data related to your browsing experience, allowing for a more personalized experience. Web beacons may also be used to monitor user behavior.</p>

                        <h3 class="fs-6 fw-bold">Types of Cookies</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>First-party Cookies</strong>: Created by our site to enhance functionality, such as remembering preferences.</li>
                            <li><strong>Third-party Cookies</strong>: Created by external services to track user behavior, often used for advertising.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Only necessary cookies require consent.</p>

                        <h3 class="fs-6 fw-bold">Which Cookies Do We Use?</h3>
                        <p>We primarily use first-party cookies to enhance your experience on our site. These cookies may track language preferences and visit duration. Third-party games may also use cookies; we recommend reviewing their privacy policies.</p>

                        <h2 class="fs-5 fw-bold">SECURITY MEASURES</h2>
                        <p>Merge Rot has implemented appropriate technical and organizational measures to secure your personal information. Access to this data is restricted to authorized personnel only. We do not sell or rent your data to third parties. Any external processors we may engage will handle your data confidentially.</p>

                        <h2 class="fs-5 fw-bold">CONTACT INFORMATION OF DATA CONTROLLER</h2>
                        <p>For inquiries or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at <strong>support@mergerot.co</strong> or through our contact form.</p>
                    </article>
                </div>
            </section>
        </main>
        <%-include('footer')%>
</body>

